# Data Sources

- Each data source lives in `src/sources/<name>/` and implements `core.DataSource`. Lifecycle capabilities are declared in `src/sources/registry/registry.go`.

## Package shape

- Typical files: `source.go`, `mcp.go`, `daemon.go`, `client.go`, `cli.go`, `store.go` / `store_init.go`, `service.go`, `helpers.go`.
- Keep source-specific business logic out of `*_init.go`.

## Required behavior

- `RunsCore=true`: sync and persist local data via subscription or polling.
- `IndexGlobally=true`: MCP read handlers use the local DB only; implement `SearchEntries()` with meaningful `Source`, `SourceID`, `ContentType`, `Title`, `Content`, and follow-up `Metadata`.
- `Reset(dataDir string)`: daemon-owned cleanup; remove source files without racing open handles.
- Persist disabled state after reset/auth loss; keep the source entry in config.

## Shared utilities

- Use `core.RunPollLoop`, `core.DefaultReset`, and `core.OpenDB` instead of duplicating boilerplate.
- Prefer interfaces and helpers over struct embedding or base types.

## Data requirements

- Capture and return all known timestamps (`created_time`, `modified_time` / `updated_time`, plus domain-specific timestamps).
- Do not auto-download or cache binary media. Store metadata and expose an explicit download/fetch tool.

## New source checklist

- Implement `core.DataSource`; add `core.CoreService` only when `RunsCore=true`.
- Accept `dataDir string` in constructors.
- Register tools with the `Name() + "_"` prefix.
- Store credentials in shared config and/or source-owned files.
